entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: A decentralized operating system focused on AI and multichain capabilities. It is developing its own L2/L3 rollup network and aims to integrate various data sources and services.

entities.name: $ai16z
entities.description: A token that is undergoing migration to the $elizaOS token.

entities.name: $elizaOS
entities.description: The native token of the ElizaOS ecosystem, functioning as a gas token on its L2/L3 network. It supports multichain operations.

entities.name: Twitter/X
entities.description: A social media platform known for its real-time information sharing and APIs. It has faced issues with API access costs and integration.

entities.name: Gabriel Aigner
entities.description: A community member who offered to help with unsuspending the ElizaOS X account.

entities.name: pump.fun API
entities.description: An API that allows users to create tokens without incurring developer fees.

entities.name: Puppeteer
entities.description: A Node library which provides a high-level API to control Chrome or Chromium over the DevTools Protocol. It is used for data scraping.

entities.name: Telegram
entities.description: A cloud-based instant messaging service that offers advanced features for communication and bot integration. It is being considered as a platform for delivering ecosystem news.

entities.name: Chainlink
entities.description: A decentralized oracle network that provides real-world data to smart contracts on the blockchain. It is used for ElizaOS's multichain strategy.

entities.name: Base
entities.description: An Ethereum-scaling L2 solution that supports multichain operations. ElizaOS plans to operate on Base and other chains.

entities.name: SPL Contract
entities.description: A token standard on the Solana blockchain. The ElizaOS token is migrating from an SPL contract.

entities.name: SVM
entities.description: Solana Virtual Machine, a component of Solana's blockchain ecosystem. The ElizaOS token will be SVM-native.

entities.name: EVM-native
entities.description: Refers to compatibility with the Ethereum Virtual Machine, allowing smart contracts to run on multiple blockchains. ElizaOS will be EVM-native.

entities.name: CCIP
entities.description: Cross-Chain Interoperability Protocol, a standard for enabling communication between different blockchains. ElizaOS will utilize CCIP.

entities.name: ERC-4337
entities.description: An Ethereum standard that enables account abstraction, making smart contract wallets function like regular user accounts. ElizaOS plans to implement an ERC-4337 paymaster system.

entities.name: ERC-8004
entities.description: A proposed Ethereum standard for decentralized application discovery. ElizaOS plans to use ERC-8004 as a discovery layer.

entities.name: Polymarket plugin
entities.description: A plugin related to the Polymarket platform, a decentralized prediction market. A GitHub repository for this plugin was shared.

entities.name: OpenRouter
entities.description: A service that provides an API gateway for accessing multiple Large Language Model (LLM) providers. They announced the beta launch of their Responses API.

entities.name: Discord
entities.description: A popular communication platform used for online communities. Discussions from ElizaOS's Discord server are analyzed.

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A web-based platform for version control and collaboration on software development projects. It hosts repositories for various plugins and development efforts.
